The paper discusses replication techniques in distributed systems, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as the paper specifically focuses on replication techniques in grid computing systems. Other relevant categories include cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DB (Databases), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and cs.SE (Software Engineering) as the paper discusses data management, performance, and sharing amongst distributed systems.
